{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: generic-hdr_ish.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a Hospital Discharge Report (HDR) in SYNDERAI's Instance
    Shorthand (ISH) format. This template is fundamentally different from
    every other template in the project:

      • Output format  : ISH (not FSH/FHIR Shorthand)
      • Section marker : %%ISH%% (not %%FSH%%)
      • No %%HEAD%% or %%HTML%% sections
      • No bag functions (addHTML_tr, emitHEAD, etc.)
      • No setInstance() calls
      • No FHIR profile declarations

  WHAT IS ISH?
    ISH (Instance Shorthand) is a SYNDERAI-specific intermediary text format
    designed for compact, human-readable representation of clinical data. It is
    simpler to author and read than FSH, and is parsed by the SYNDERAI PHP
    pipeline to produce FSH instances. This template sits at the INPUT end of
    the pipeline for HDR data: PHP data arrays → Twig → ISH → SYNDERAI → FSH.

    The other templates in this directory are OUTPUT templates that convert PHP
    data into FSH. This template converts PHP data into ISH — an intermediate
    representation that another SYNDERAI process will subsequently convert into
    the FSH instances (composition, encounter, conditions, etc.) that the HDR
    bundle templates then assemble.

  ISH FORMAT OVERVIEW
    ISH uses a hierarchical keyword-indent structure:

      top-level-entity           ← entity declaration (no value)
        property value           ← scalar property
        property* value          ← multi-value / array property (see * notation)
        sub-entity               ← nested entity (indented under parent)
          property value

      section*                   ← append a new section (multiple allowed)
        type  typename
        code  $system#code Display
        title Title text
        text """multi-line text here"""

        entry*                   ← append a new entry within a section
          type  typename
          date  YYYY-MM-DD
          code* $system#code Display  ← multi-value code
          text* Display text          ← multi-value text

    Key ISH syntax rules:
      • Indentation (spaces) like yaml establishes parent–child relationships.
      • `*` suffix on a keyword means the property or block may appear multiple
        times (analogous to FSH's `[+]` append operator).
      • Values follow immediately after the keyword, space-separated.
      • Codes use `$system#code Display` notation (unquoted display text).
      • Multi-line text values use triple double-quotes `"""…"""`.
      • Lines beginning with `#` are ISH comments (these appear in the output
        and are processed by the ISH parser, unlike Twig `{ # # }` comments
        which are stripped before output).

  %%ISH%% SECTION MARKER
    The `%%ISH%%` marker replaces the `%%FSH%%` marker used by all other
    templates. It signals to the SYNDERAI pre-processor that what follows is
    ISH-format content rather than FSH. The SYNDERAI script routes the
    section to a different processing pipeline accordingly. There are no
    companion `%%HEAD%%` or `%%HTML%%` markers in ISH templates — the ISH
    format has no equivalent of the HTML bag concept.

  OUTPUT STRUCTURE — TOP-LEVEL BLOCKS
    The template always emits these blocks unconditionally:
      patient     — demographics, geolocation, address
      encounter   — episode dates and primary reason
      hospital    — organisation name, address, and treating practitioner

    The template conditionally emits these section blocks (each as `section*`):
      synthesis         — brief discharge summary text (when discharge.text present)
      hospitalcourse    — hospital course narrative (always)
      pharmacotherapy   — medications during the encounter (when medication present)
      dischargediagnosis — diagnoses at discharge (when discharge present)
      procedures        — significant procedures (when procedure present)
      vitalsigns        — vital signs during stay (when vitalsigns present)

  PATIENT BLOCK — UNIQUE ISH FIELDS
    Two fields appear in this template that are absent from all FSH patient
    templates:

    nameset   — the patient's language / locale identifier (e.g. "DE", "NL").
                Maps to `patient.language`. Used by the ISH parser to select
                the correct name ordering conventions and display language.

    latitude  — patient's geographic latitude (decimal degrees).
    longitude — patient's geographic longitude (decimal degrees).
                Both used by SYNDERAI to automatically detect the nearest
                hospital from the data — the ISH comment
                `# closest hospital will be dectected by SYNDERAI` documents
                this intent.

    Only `street1` is included in the address (not street2 or street3).

  ENCOUNTER BLOCK — FLAT REASON OBJECT
    Unlike the encounter in encounter-eu-hdr_fsh.twig where `encounter.reason`
    is an array of objects iterated in a loop, this template receives the
    primary reason as a flat top-level `reason` object with `.system`, `.code`,
    and `.display` fields. Only one reason is emitted per encounter:
      reason* {{ reason.system }}#{{ reason.code }} {{ reason.display }}
    The `*` suffix signals to the ISH parser that a reason line may appear
    multiple times if needed, even though only one is emitted here.

  HOSPITAL PRACTITIONER SUB-BLOCK
    The practitioner is represented as a named sub-block (`practitioner`) nested
    under `hospital`. This differs from the FSH provider templates where
    Practitioner is a separate top-level FHIR resource. The sub-block is only
    emitted when `hospital.practitioner.family` is non-empty.
    `hospital.practitioner.gender` is unique to this template — not present
    in the FSH provider templates.

  MEDICATION SECTION — CODING PRIORITY
    Same SNOMED-preferred, RxNorm-fallback pattern as medicationstatement-eu-eps:
      SNOMED present → `code $sct#code display`
      SNOMED absent  → `code $rxnorm#code display` (⚠ typo — see Issue #1)
    `m.snomed.preferredTerm` is always emitted as the `text` property of each
    medication entry regardless of which code system was used. No conditional
    guard — the caller must always supply a preferredTerm.

  DISCHARGE DIAGNOSIS — ICD-10 CODING
    Unlike the FSH condition templates which use SNOMED CT, the discharge
    diagnosis in ISH uses ICD-10:
      code* $icd10#{{ discharge.code }} {{ discharge.display }}
    The `*` on `code*` signals a potentially multi-valued code property.
    `discharge.code` is a flat string (ICD-10 code), not a system/code object.
    The entry uses `encounter.episodeend` as the `start` date (the date of
    discharge is treated as the onset date of the discharge diagnosis).

  PROCEDURES — PREFERREDTERM AS PRIMARY CODE LABEL
    The ISH procedure entry uses `p.code.preferredTerm` for the `code*` label
    and `p.code.display` for `text*`. This is the reverse of the typical FSH
    convention where `display` is used in the code expression and `preferredTerm`
    overrides the `.text` element. Both are conditional on being non-empty.
    The date filter `p.date|date('Y-m-d')` is the only date filter applied in
    this template — all other dates are passed through raw.

  VITAL SIGNS — TWO-LEVEL NESTED LOOP
    `vitalsigns` is a nested associative structure:
      Level 1: `{% for d, vblock in vitalsigns %}` — key-value dict iteration.
               `d` is the grouping key (e.g. date or category label).
               `vblock` is an array of individual readings for that group.
      Level 2: `{% for v in vblock %}` — iterates individual readings.
    Each reading carries: `v.date`, `v.code` (system, code, display), and
    `v.value` (value, system, code, unit). The value line emits all Quantity
    sub-fields on a single ISH line:
      value {{ v.value.value }} {{ v.value.system }}#{{ v.value.code }} "{{ v.value.unit }}"
    Note: `d` (the outer key) is never referenced in the output — see Issue #3.

  COMMENTED-OUT ADMISSION EVALUATION SECTION
    A block of ISH content documenting an admission evaluation section is
    wrapped in a Twig block comment. The block uses `#` ISH comment markers
    within the Twig comment:
      { #
       # admission evaluation
       # section*
       #   type admissionevaluation
       ...
      # }
    This is ISH-formatted content inside a Twig comment — none of it appears
    in the output. It serves as a development placeholder documenting the
    intended structure of a future admission evaluation section.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                             │ Type     │ Description                                  │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ patient.name                         │ string   │ Full display name (ISH comment header only). │
  │ patient.birthdate                    │ string   │ ISO 8601 date of birth.                      │
  │ patient.given                        │ string[] │ Array of given names; one given* per entry.  │
  │ patient.family                       │ string   │ Family / surname.                            │
  │ patient.gender                       │ string   │ Gender code.                                 │
  │ patient.postcode                     │ string?  │ Postal code (conditional).                   │
  │ patient.city                         │ string?  │ City name (conditional).                     │
  │ patient.street1                      │ string?  │ Street address line 1 (conditional).         │
  │ patient.countrycode                  │ string   │ ISO 3166-1 country code.                     │
  │ patient.phone                        │ string   │ Phone number.                                │
  │ patient.language                     │ string   │ Language / locale identifier (→ nameset).    │
  │ patient.latitude                     │ number   │ Geographic latitude (decimal degrees).       │
  │ patient.longitude                    │ number   │ Geographic longitude (decimal degrees).      │
  │ encounter.episodestart               │ string   │ Encounter episode start date (no ?? fallback)│
  │ encounter.episodeend                 │ string   │ Encounter episode end date (no ?? fallback). │
  │ encounter.hospitalCourse             │ string   │ Hospital course narrative text.              │
  │ reason.system                        │ string   │ CodeSystem URI for the encounter reason.     │
  │ reason.code                          │ string   │ Encounter reason concept code.               │
  │ reason.display                       │ string   │ Encounter reason display text.               │
  │ hospital.name                        │ string   │ Hospital organisation name.                  │
  │ hospital.street                      │ string?  │ Hospital street (conditional).               │
  │ hospital.city                        │ string?  │ Hospital city (conditional).                 │
  │ hospital.postcode                    │ string?  │ Hospital postal code (conditional).          │
  │ hospital.country                     │ string   │ Hospital country code.                       │
  │ hospital.practitioner.family         │ string?  │ Practitioner family name; gates the sub-block│
  │ hospital.practitioner.prefix         │ string?  │ Practitioner prefix (conditional).           │
  │ hospital.practitioner.given          │ string[] │ Array of given names; one given* per entry.  │
  │ hospital.practitioner.gender         │ string   │ Practitioner gender (unique to ISH).         │
  │ discharge                            │ object?  │ Discharge data; empty = omit sections.       │
  │   .text                              │ string?  │   Synthesis / summary text (conditional).    │
  │   .code                              │ string   │   ICD-10 discharge diagnosis code.           │
  │   .display                           │ string   │   Discharge diagnosis display text.          │
  │ medication                           │ object[]?│ Array of medication objects (conditional).   │
  │   [n].snomed.code                    │ string?  │   SNOMED CT code (preferred).                │
  │   [n].snomed.display                 │ string   │   SNOMED display.                            │
  │   [n].snomed.preferredTerm           │ string   │   Preferred term (always used as text).      │
  │   [n].rxnorm.code                    │ string?  │   RxNorm code (fallback; ⚠ typo in template).│
  │   [n].rxnorm.display                 │ string   │   RxNorm display.                            │
  │   [n].start                          │ string?  │   Medication start date (⚠ see Issue #2).   │
  │ procedure                            │ object[]?│ Array of procedure objects (conditional).    │
  │   [n].date                           │ string?  │   Procedure date; filtered Y-m-d.            │
  │   [n].code.system                    │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                            │
  │   [n].code.code                      │ string   │   Procedure concept code.                    │
  │   [n].code.preferredTerm             │ string   │   Preferred term (→ code* value in ISH).     │
  │   [n].code.display                   │ string?  │   Display text (→ text* value; conditional). │
  │ vitalsigns                           │ dict     │ Nested dict: grouping key → vblock array.    │
  │   [d]                                │ string   │   Grouping key (declared but never used).    │
  │   [d][n].date                        │ string   │   Vital sign observation date.               │
  │   [d][n].code.system                 │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                            │
  │   [d][n].code.code                   │ string   │   Observation concept code.                  │
  │   [d][n].code.display                │ string   │   Observation code display.                  │
  │   [d][n].value.value                 │ number   │   Numeric measurement value.                 │
  │   [d][n].value.system                │ string   │   Unit system URI (usually UCUM).            │
  │   [d][n].value.code                  │ string   │   UCUM unit code.                            │
  │   [d][n].value.unit                  │ string   │   Human-readable unit string (quoted).       │
  └──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED (ISH notation: $system#code)
    $sct     — SNOMED CT; medication codes, procedure codes
    $rxnorm  — RxNorm; medication codes (fallback; ⚠ affected by typo)
    $loinc   — LOINC; section type codes (synthesis, hospitalcourse, etc.)
    $icd10   — ICD-10; discharge diagnosis code

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-12-08, rev 2026-03-17
  ============================================================================
#}

%%ISH%%
{#
  ── ISH output begins immediately after the %%ISH%% marker ──────────────────
  Lines beginning with # below are ISH comments that appear in the output
  and are processed by the ISH parser. They differ from Twig { # # } comments,
  which are stripped before the ISH parser ever sees the content.
#}
# HDR in ISH format for {{ patient.name }}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  PATIENT BLOCK
  Unique ISH-only fields: nameset (language/locale), latitude, longitude.
  Only street1 is included — street2/street3 are not emitted.
  latitude/longitude enable SYNDERAI to detect the nearest hospital automatically.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
# patient
patient
  birthdate {{ patient.birthdate }}
{% for g in patient.given %}
  given* {{ g }}
{% endfor %}
  family {{ patient.family }}
  gender {{ patient.gender }}
{% if patient.postcode is not empty %}
  postcode {{ patient.postcode }}
{% endif %}
{% if patient.city is not empty %}
  city {{ patient.city }}
{% endif %}
{% if patient.street1 is not empty %}
  street {{ patient.street1 }}
{% endif %}
  country {{ patient.countrycode }}
  phone {{ patient.phone }}
  nameset {{ patient.language }}
  latitude {{ patient.latitude }}
  longitude {{ patient.longitude }}
# closest hospital will be dectected by SYNDERAI
# the provider person in the hopital as primary contact person will be dectected by SYNDERAI

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  ENCOUNTER BLOCK
  Uses episodestart/episodeend directly — no ?? coalescing with start/end.
  ⚠ See Issue #4: caller must supply the episode variants, not start/end.
  reason is a flat top-level object (not encounter.reason[] array).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
# encounter
encounter
  start {{ encounter.episodestart ?? encounter.start }}
  end {{ encounter.episodeend ?? encounter.end }}
  reason* {{ reason.system }}#{{ reason.code }} {{ reason.display }}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  HOSPITAL BLOCK
  Practitioner sub-block gated on hospital.practitioner.family being non-empty.
  hospital.practitioner.gender is unique to this ISH template.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
# hospital
hospital
  name {{ hospital.name }}
{% if hospital.street is not empty %}
  street {{ hospital.street }}
{% endif %}
{% if hospital.city is not empty %}
  city {{ hospital.city }}
{% endif %}
{% if hospital.postcode is not empty %}
  postcode {{ hospital.postcode }}
{% endif %}
  country {{ hospital.country }}
{% if hospital.practitioner.family is not empty %}
  practitioner
{% if hospital.practitioner.prefix is not empty %}
    prefix {{ hospital.practitioner.prefix }}
{% endif %}
{% for g in hospital.practitioner.given %}
    given* {{ g }}
{% endfor %}
    family {{ hospital.practitioner.family }}
    gender {{ hospital.practitioner.gender }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Commented-out admission evaluation section ───────────────────────────────
  ISH-formatted content inside a Twig comment — not emitted.
  Documents the intended structure for a future admission evaluation section.
  Lines use # (ISH comment style) within the Twig { # ... # } block.
  Note: Twig comments cannot be nested, so the inner { # populate ... # } style
  is not used here — plain # markers are used instead.
#}
{#
 # admission evaluation
 # section*
 #   type admissionevaluation
 #   code $loinc#67852-4 Hospital Admission evaluation note
 #   title Admission evaluation
 #   text """TEXT"""
 #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  SYNTHESIS SECTION (conditional on discharge.text)
  Brief discharge summary text. The ISH comment lines within this block
  appear in the output when discharge.text is present.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% if discharge.text is not empty %}
# Synthesis
# short discharge summary text of this encounter episode
# synthesis
section*
  type synthesis
  code $loinc#67781-5 Summarization of encounter note
  title Synthesis
  text """{{ discharge.text }}"""
{% endif %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  HOSPITAL COURSE SECTION (always emitted)
  encounter.hospitalCourse is a required field — no conditional guard.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
# Hospital Course
section*
  type hospitalcourse
  code $loinc#8648-8 Hospital course note
  text """{{ encounter.hospitalCourse }}"""

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  PHARMACOTHERAPY SECTION (conditional on medication being non-empty)
  Each medication produces one entry* block.

  Coding priority: SNOMED preferred; RxNorm fallback (when SNOMED absent).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% if medication is not empty %}
# medications associated with this encounter episode
section*
  type pharmacotherapy
  code $loinc#87232-5 Medication administration.brief
  title Medications
{% for m in medication %}
  entry*
    type medication
{% if m.start is not empty %}
    start {{ m.start }}
{% endif %}
{# SNOMED preferred; RxNorm fallback #}
{% if m.snomed.code is not empty %}
    code $sct#{{ m.snomed.code }} {{ m.snomed.display }}
{% else %}
{# RxNorm fallback — ⚠ typo: medmication should be medication #}
{% if m.rxnorm.code is not empty %}
    code $rxnorm#{{ m.rxnorm.code }} {{ m.rxnorm.display }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% if m.snomed.preferredTerm is not empty %}
    text {{ m.snomed.preferredTerm }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %} {# medication loop #}
{% endif %}  {# if medications at all #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  DISCHARGE DIAGNOSIS SECTION (conditional on discharge being non-empty)
  Uses ICD-10 coding ($icd10), not SNOMED CT — different from FSH condition
  templates. encounter.episodeend is used as the condition start date.
  discharge.code is a flat string (not a system/code object).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% if discharge is not empty %}
# discharge diagnoses of this encounter episode
section*
  type dischargediagnosis
  code $loinc#11535-2 Hospital discharge diagnosis note
  title Diagnosis at Discharge
  entry*
    type condition
    start {{ encounter.episodeend }}
    code* $icd10#{{ discharge.code }} {{ discharge.display }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  PROCEDURES SECTION (conditional on procedure being non-empty)
  p.code.preferredTerm → code* value (primary identifier in ISH)
  p.code.display       → text* value (descriptive label; conditional)
  Note: preferredTerm and display roles are REVERSED relative to FSH convention
  where display appears in the code expression and preferredTerm overrides text.
  The |date('Y-m-d') filter is the only date filter in this template.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% if procedure is not empty %}
# significant sectionSignificantProcedures
section*
  type procedures
  code $loinc#10185-7 Hospital discharge procedure note
  title Significant procedures
{% for p in procedure %}
  entry*
    type procedure
{% if p.date is not empty %}
{% set pdate = p.date|date('Y-m-d') %}
    date {{ pdate }}
{% endif %}
    code* {{ p.code.system }}#{{ p.code.code }} {{ p.code.preferredTerm }}
{% if p.code.display is not empty %}
    text* {{ p.code.display }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %} {# procedure loop #}
{% endif %}  {# if procedures at all #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  VITAL SIGNS SECTION (conditional on vitalsigns being non-empty)
  vitalsigns is a two-level nested structure:
    Level 1: {% for vblock in vitalsigns %} — key-value dict
             `vblock` is an array of readings.
    Level 2: {% for v in vblock %} — individual readings.
  Value line: all Quantity sub-fields on one ISH line, unit in double-quotes.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% if vitalsigns is not empty %}
# vital signs
section*
  type vitalsigns
  code $loinc#8716-3 Vital signs note
  title Vital Signs during Stay
{% for vblock in vitalsigns %}
{% for v in vblock %}
  entry*
    type vitalsign
    date {{ v.date }}
    code* {{ v.code.system }}#{{ v.code.code }} {{ v.code.display }}
    value {{ v.value.value }} {{ v.value.system }}#{{ v.value.code }} "{{ v.value.unit }}"
{% endfor %} {# vitalsigns loop #}
{% endfor %} {# vblock loop #}
{% endif %}  {# if vitalsigns at all #}
